comments: Gobert (UTA) extends his arm out and delivers contact to Clarke's (MEM) back, which affects his ability to set his intended pick.
Mitchell (UTA) legally contests Bane's (MEM) jump shot attempt.
Bane (MEM) moves alongside Mitchell's (UTA) path, and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Clarke (MEM) legally contests Bogdanovic's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Morant (MEM) slides his pivot foot to create space from the defensive pressure.
Gobert (UTA) retreats along Morant's (MEM) path and absorbs the contact created by Morant before making clean ball contact to block his driving shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) jumps into and makes contact with Morant's (MEM) body, which affects his play at the basket.
Bane (MEM) legally contests Bogdanovic's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) releases from the contact with Clarke (MEM) as the long rebound flies over their heads.
Conley (UTA) makes clean ball contact to poke it loose from Williams (MEM) on his steal attempt.
Gobert (UTA) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Bane (MEM) and cleanly blocks the shot.
Bogdanovic (UTA) jumps into and makes contact with Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) body, which affects his play at the basket.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) extends his arm out and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Mitchell's (UTA) arm, which doesn't affect his SQBR to start his drive.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position on Mitchell (UTA) and Mitchell dribbles the ball off of his own foot to lose control.

Morant (MEM) gains control of the loose ball and starts his transition play up the court when incidental contact occurs with O'Neale's (UTA) face after he went to the ground to pursue the loose ball.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Conley (UTA) makes contact with Morant's (MEM) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.

The Replay Center overturns the call on the court of an offensive goaltend as the ball no longer has a chance to score when it is touched. The ruling is an inadvertent whistle and a jump ball between any two players at center court.
Morant (MEM) gathers the ball with two hands and takes a legal two steps before releasing his pass.
Conley (UTA) makes clean hand on ball contact during his steal attempt at the end of Morant's (MEM) drive.
Morant (MEM) gathers the ball and takes two legal steps before passing.
Clarke (MEM) could be deemed to be in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Mitchell (UTA) releases from the contact with Bane (MEM) at the end of his drive.
Bane (MEM) legally contests Mitchell's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) wraps his arm around Gobert's (UTA) back while also grabbing his arm, which restricts Gobert's ability to pursue the rebound.
